ad.\nAffected Metrics: CPU, latency, load, rr, rt, trace, utilization\nRoot Cause Category: The root cause of the incident is a sudden spike in CPU usage on pod MG01, which began at 2021-03-12 15:10:00 CST. This high CPU utilization was likel\nFailure Pattern: The root cause of the incident is a sudden spike in CPU usage on pod MG01, which began at 2021-03-12 15:10:00 CST. This high CPU utilization was likely triggered by increased processing load originating from upstream services, particularly observed in downstream trace delays from dockerB2 to MG01 and correlated with elevated system-level CPU metrics (CPUUserTime, CPUCpuUtil, CPULoad) on MG01. The anomaly persisted over several minutes, indicating sustained load rather than a transient spike.\nMitigation Principles: Investigate recent deployments or configuration changes to MG01 or its upstream callers (especially dockerB2) prior to 15:10:00 CST.; Implement CPU throttling and horizontal pod autoscaling for MG01 based on CPU usage thresholds.; Add monitoring alerts on trace duration increases from upstream services to detect early signs of service degradation.; Conduct a load test to simulate traffic patterns observed during the incident to validate system resilience.\n\nBackgroud:\n"\n\n\nBased on this information, identify the MOST LIKELY root cause component and reason from the candidate list.\nFollow these rules:\n- The root cause must be a single component from the candidate list.\n- The reason must be directly supported by the anomaly description.\n- Assign a suspicious score between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher = more confident).\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format:\n{\n    "component": "service-name",\n    "reason": "brief reason",\n    "score": 0.92\n}'}]
